815// Convert camera sample to I420 with cropping, rotation and vertical flip.
816// "src_size" is needed to parse MJPG.
817// "dst_stride_y" number of bytes in a row of the dst_y plane.
818// Normally this would be the same as dst_width, with recommended alignment
819// to 16 bytes for better efficiency.
820// If rotation of 90 or 270 is used, stride is affected. The caller should
821// allocate the I420 buffer according to rotation.
822// "dst_stride_u" number of bytes in a row of the dst_u plane.
823// Normally this would be the same as (dst_width + 1) / 2, with
824// recommended alignment to 16 bytes for better efficiency.
825// If rotation of 90 or 270 is used, stride is affected.
826// "crop_x" and "crop_y" are starting position for cropping.
827// To center, crop_x = (src_width - dst_width) / 2
828// crop_y = (src_height - dst_height) / 2
829// "src_width" / "src_height" is size of src_frame in pixels.
830// "src_height" can be negative indicating a vertically flipped image source.
831// "crop_width" / "crop_height" is the size to crop the src to.
832// Must be less than or equal to src_width/src_height
833// Cropping parameters are pre-rotation.
834// "rotation" can be 0, 90, 180 or 270.
835// "fourcc" is a fourcc. ie 'I420', 'YUY2'
836// Returns 0 for successful; -1 for invalid parameter. Non-zero for failure.
837LIBYUV_API
838int ConvertToI420(const uint8_t* sample,
839 size_t sample_size,
840 uint8_t* dst_y,
841 int dst_stride_y,
842 uint8_t* dst_u,
843 int dst_stride_u,
844 uint8_t* dst_v,
845 int dst_stride_v,
846 int crop_x,
847 int crop_y,
848 int src_width,
849 int src_height,
850 int crop_width,
851 int crop_height,
852 enum RotationMode rotation,
853 uint32_t fourcc);
